relation: Governor's Job Fair - In Observation of the 14th Annual Workforce Development in Florida Location: Central Florida Fair Grounds, Orlando FL Are you looking for a new job? Find your next employer at Central Florida Employment Council’s (CFEC) job fair in Orlando, Florida, from 12-4 p.m. Over 75 companies offering thousands of career openings in various industries and resources on hand to assist your job search. PROFESSIONAL DRESS, bring resumes, free admission/parking, and no children, please. For additional information and job seeker preregistration, please visit Central Florida Employment Council (CFEC). Also, for any question, please call Christian HELP/CFEC at 407.834.4022. View Map & Details

Monty Python's SPAMALOT Location: Lowndes Shakespeare Center, Orlando FL Orlando Shakespeare Theater invites you to come see Monty Python’s SPAMALOT! (Recommend for ages 13 and up) this saucy musical parody tells the legendary tale of King Arthur and the Knights of the Round Table. On a quest for the Holy Grail, the Knights encounter flying cows, killer rabbits, and taunting Frenchmen while performing heart-stopping musical numbers. Winner of three Tony Awards including “Best Musical”, SPAMALOT elevates silliness to an art form. For specific times, dates and to purchase tickets, visit: Monty Pythons Spamalot Webpage. View Map & Details

Monty Python's SPAMALOT Location: Orlando Shakespeare Theater, Orlando FL Lovingly ripped off from the classic film Monty Python and The Holy Grail, this saucy musical parody tells the legendary tale of King Arthur and the Knights of the Round Table. On a quest for the Holy Grail, the Knights encounter flying cows, killer rabbits, and taunting Frenchmen while performing heart-stopping musical numbers. Winner of three Tony Awards including “Best Musical”, SPAMALOT elevates silliness to an art form. Tickets and additional information can be found at Orlando Shakespeare Theater. View Map & Details

Inspired For Life Women's Conference Location: First Church Melbourne, Melbourne Florida We all need to be encouraged, energized and renewed. First Church Melbourne invites you to join us for a weekend of laughter, hope, and story as we gain a new perspective that will leave us “Inspired for Life!” Together, we will hear from three incredible women on their own journey toward inspiration, have break-out sessions of fun and learning that will enrich our lives, and experience life-giving worship through music and Holy Communion. We hope you will invite friends and register together. A new perspective for all of us is on the horizon this September, so don’t miss it! Conference Dates and Times: – Friday, Sept. 11 from 6 p.m. – 9 p.m. – Saturday, Sept. 12 from 8:30 a.m. – 3 p.m. For more information and to register for the conference, visit First Church Melbourne’s website. View Map & Details

Disney's Night of Joy - Day 1 - Ticketed Location: Disney’s Magic Kingdom®, Lake Buena Vista FL Disney’s Night of Joy is a two night contemporary Christian music festival held at Magic Kingdom® Park on September 11 and 12, from 7:00 p.m. to 1:00 a.m. You’ll have the chance to see live performances by Christian music artists including some heard right here on Z88.3. There will be stages set up throughout the park including one at Cinderella’s Castle! When you’re not listening to music, you can ride some of your favorite classic rides at Magic Kingdom® Park! The Z Crew will be there. We hope you can join us, too! To get more details about this event and purchase tickets, please visit Disney’s Night of Joy website! View Map & Details

Lady Lake Health & Senior Expo Location: American Legion Post 347, Lady Lake FL Join us for a fun and informative event celebrating seniors! There will be free health screenings, bingo, workshops, free samples, shopping opportunities, community services, and more. Learn about senior living, retirement, holistic health, nutrition, travel and leisure, and health and wellness. Parking and admission are both free, so bring a friend! For more information, call 386-860-0092 or visit Buckler Promotions’s website. View Map & Details

Living Proof Live Simulcast with Beth Moore Location: Edgewater Alliance Church, Edgewater FL We are excited to be hosting the Living Proof Live Simulcast with Beth Moore! Come join us for a day in the Word as we worship together. The event both challenges and encourages women to grow deeper in faith. We’ll be joining women around the world for this live, global, internet streaming event! Dove Award winning musical artist, Travis Cottrell, is slated to lead worship. The Living Proof Live Simulcast kicks-off on Saturday, September 12, 2015, at 10:30 a.m. and ends at 5:15 p.m. Doors open at 9:30 a.m. Early-Bird ticket price is $20 through August 15th ($25 August 16-31). Tickets can be purchased online at Edgewater Alliance Church under “Events” or by contacting Doris Swift at the church office, Monday-Thursday 9 a.m.-4 p.m. at: 386.427.0385. Ticket price includes a continental breakfast, lunch, and listening guide. There will also be numerous drawings for door prizes throughout the day. Grab some friends and make it a girl’s weekend! There will be no childcare for this event. We look forward to welcoming you! View Map & Details

O-Town MacDown Cooking Competition: Benefits Give Kids The World Location: Osceola Heritage Park, Kissimmee FL O-Town MacDown is a creative mac-n-cheese cooking competition, held between local professional chefs and restaurants. This family-oriented event will include activities for kids, continuous stage entertainment, assorted vendor booths, and of course, delicious mac-n-cheese. Competition is open to professional chefs and local restaurants. Attendance and participation benefits Give Kids The World Village*. The event will include: ALL-you-can-eat Mac-n-Cheese! Live Entertainment. Celebrity Chef Cooking Demonstrations. Kids’ Fun Zone including face painting, macaroni art station and character meet-and-greets. Vendor Booths. FREE parking. Cost: $10 for Adults (or $15 at the door). $5 for Kids (or $10 at the door). *Give Kids The World Village is a 74-acre, nonprofit “storybook” resort in Central Florida. Children with life-threatening illnesses and their families are treated to weeklong, cost-free vacations, complete with accommodations, donated attraction tickets, meals and more. Since 1986, Give Kids The World Village has welcomed more than 138,000 families. For more information, visit Give Kids The World. View Map & Details

The Gift of Life Charity Gala/A Night at The Tropicana Location: The Wyndham Orlando Resort, Orlando FL Location: The Wyndham Orlando Resort, Orlando FL You are cordially invited to attend The Gift of Life’s Annual Charity Gala Hosted by Wyndham Orlando Resort and John Michael Events. Event will benefit premature babies and families Dinner, entertainment and auction Cost: Tickets are $45.00/Adults Kids $25.00/Babysitting and entertainment available for children Group purchase and corporate sponsorships available upon request. RSVP by purchase of your ticket by 9.1.15 at the The Gift of Life’s Annual Charity Gala. Contact The Gift of Life for questions at: info@thegiftoflife27.org or 407.905.5454 Keep up with event details on our Facebook page. Because life is a gift, we treasure each moment…….. View Map & Details
